SYNTAX

for(int i = 0; testExpression; updateExpression) {
//code inside the for loop
}

PROJECT
Can you use the for loop to compute the sum of only odd numbers from 1 to 100?

in each interaction,you will need to add an odd number to the sum.

#include <stdio.h>

int main() {
  int sum = 0;
  
  for(int i = 1; i <= 100; i = i + 2){
      sum = sum + i;
  }
 
 printf("%d\n",sum);
    return 0;
}

OUTPUT
2500
